This paper deals with State Machine Replication (SMR) solutions, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Computer Networks (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the message and time complexity of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Control and Optimization (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with Byzantine SMR solutions, which are studied in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
